Hodge Auto Centre, a subsidiary Of Hardely Grey Group Of Companies, says it has opened a workshop with modern facilities in the Lekki area of Lagos State. The auto firm also said it had opened its main office named after the mother of its Chief Executive Officer, Kenasolibe Emeasoba. The workshop was opened in Lagos on last Saturday, according to a statement by the company. The spokesperson, Hardely Grey Group of Companies, Josephine Atabohwho, was quoted as saying that the organisation would continue with the tradition of giving quality service to its teeming customers by providing satisfactory excellent automobile maintenance and repairs. During the opening, Atabohwho said guests were taken to all sections of the workshop to examine the new facilities in the centre. Speaking during the tour, the statement quoted the spokesperson as saying, “This is the workshop where diverse repairs on all kinds of vehicles are done. When customers come in with their vehicles, the first thing we do is to get down all their details at the office. The vehicles are then taken to the workshop for examination.’’ The management of the company also opened its main office building with a memorial lecture in honour of late Dr Uche Regina Benedette Emeasoba. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com